305 """
306 from_interprocedural!(interp::AbstractInterpreter, rt, sv::AbsIntState,
307 arginfo::ArgInfo, maybecondinfo) -> newrt
308
309 Converts inter-procedural return type `rt` into a local lattice element `newrt`,
310 that is appropriate in the context of current local analysis frame `sv`, especially:
311 - unwraps `rt::LimitedAccuracy` and collects its limitations into the current frame `sv`
312 - converts boolean `rt` to new boolean `newrt` in a way `newrt` can propagate extra conditional
313 refinement information, e.g. translating `rt::InterConditional` into `newrt::Conditional`
314 that holds a type constraint information about a variable in `sv`
315
316 This function _should_ be used wherever we propagate results returned from
317 `abstract_call_method` or `abstract_call_method_with_const_args`.
318
319 When `maybecondinfo !== nothing`, this function also tries extra conditional argument type refinement.
320 In such cases `maybecondinfo` should be either of:
321 - `maybecondinfo::Tuple{Vector{Any},Vector{Any}}`: precomputed argument type refinement information
322 - method call signature tuple type
323 When we deal with multiple `MethodMatch`es, it's better to precompute `maybecondinfo` by
324 `tmerge`ing argument signature type of each method call.
325 """

656 function edge_matches_sv(interp::AbstractInterpreter, frame::AbsIntState,
657 method::Method, @nospecialize(sig), sparams::SimpleVector,
658 hardlimit::Bool, sv::AbsIntState)
659 # The `method_for_inference_heuristics` will expand the given method's generator if
660 # necessary in order to retrieve this field from the generated `CodeInfo`, if it exists.
661 # The other `CodeInfo`s we inspect will already have this field inflated, so we just
662 # access it directly instead (to avoid regeneration).
663 world = get_world_counter(interp)
664 callee_method2 = method_for_inference_heuristics(method, sig, sparams, world) # Union{Method, Nothing}
665
666 inf_method2 = method_for_inference_limit_heuristics(frame) # limit only if user token match
667 inf_method2 isa Method || (inf_method2 = nothing)
668 if callee_method2 !== inf_method2
669 return false
670 end
671 if !hardlimit || InferenceParams(interp).ignore_recursion_hardlimit
672 # if this is a soft limit,
673 # also inspect the parent of this edge,
674 # to see if they are the same Method as sv
675 # in which case we'll need to ensure it is convergent
676 # otherwise, we don't
677
678 # check in the cycle list first
679 # all items in here are mutual parents of all others
680 if !any(p::AbsIntState->matches_sv(p, sv), callers_in_cycle(frame))
681 let parent = frame_parent(frame)
682 parent !== nothing || return false
683 (is_cached(parent) || frame_parent(parent) !== nothing) || return false
684 matches_sv(parent, sv) || return false
685 end
686 end
687
688 # If the method defines a recursion relation, give it a chance
689 # to tell us that this recursion is actually ok.
690 if isdefined(method, :recursion_relation)
691 if Core._apply_pure(method.recursion_relation, Any[method, callee_method2, sig, frame_instance(frame).specTypes])
692 return false
693 end
694 end
695 end
696 return true
697 end

968 function const_prop_entry_heuristic(interp::AbstractInterpreter, result::MethodCallResult,
969 si::StmtInfo, sv::AbsIntState, force::Bool)
970 if result.rt isa LimitedAccuracy
971 # optimizations like inlining are disabled for limited frames,
972 # thus there won't be much benefit in constant-prop' here
973 # N.B. don't allow forced constprop' for safety (xref #52763)
974 add_remark!(interp, sv, "[constprop] Disabled by entry heuristic (limited accuracy)")
975 return false
976 elseif force
977 return true
978 elseif call_result_unused(si) && result.edgecycle
979 add_remark!(interp, sv, "[constprop] Disabled by entry heuristic (edgecycle with unused result)")
980 return false
981 end
982 # check if this return type is improvable (i.e. whether it's possible that with more
983 # information, we might get a more precise type)
984 rt = result.rt
985 if isa(rt, Type)
986 # could always be improved to `Const`, `PartialStruct` or just a more precise type,
987 # unless we're already at `Bottom`
988 if rt === Bottom
989 add_remark!(interp, sv, "[constprop] Disabled by entry heuristic (erroneous result)")
990 return false
991 end
992 return true
993 elseif isa(rt, PartialStruct) || isa(rt, InterConditional) || isa(rt, InterMustAlias)
994 # could be improved to `Const` or a more precise wrapper
995 return true

1113 # This is a heuristic to avoid trying to const prop through complicated functions
1114 # where we would spend a lot of time, but are probably unlikely to get an improved
1115 # result anyway.
1116 function const_prop_methodinstance_heuristic(interp::AbstractInterpreter,

1122 # anything at all without const-propping, so the inlining check below
1123 # isn't particularly helpful here.

1127 # information we have here would be discarded if it is not inlined into a callee context

1131 return true

1133 flag = get_curr_ssaflag(sv)
1134 if is_stmt_inline(flag)

1136 # since the inliner will try to find this constant result
1137 # if these constant arguments arrive there

1294 # This is only for use with `Conditional`.
1295 # In general, usage of this is wrong.
1296 function ssa_def_slot(@nospecialize(arg), sv::InferenceState)
1297 code = sv.src.code
1298 init = sv.currpc
1299 while isa(arg, SSAValue)
1300 init = arg.id
1301 arg = code[init]
1302 end
1303 if arg isa SlotNumber
1304 # found this kind of pattern:
1305 # %init = SlotNumber(x)
1306 # [...]
1307 # goto if not isa(%init, T)
1308 # now conservatively make sure there isn't potentially another conflicting assignment
1309 # to the same slot between the def and usage
1310 # we can assume the IR is sorted, since the front-end only creates SSA values in order
1311 for i = init:(sv.currpc-1)
1312 e = code[i]
1313 if isexpr(e, :(=)) && e.args[1] === arg
1314 return nothing
1315 end
1316 end
1317 else
1318 # there might still be the following kind of pattern (see #45499):
1319 # %init = ...
1320 # [...]
1321 # SlotNumber(x) = %init
1322 # [...]
1323 # goto if not isa(%init, T)
1324 # let's check if there is a slot assigned to the def SSA value but also there isn't
1325 # any potentially conflicting assignment to the same slot
1326 arg = nothing
1327 def = SSAValue(init)
1328 for i = (init+1):(sv.currpc-1)
1329 e = code[i]
1330 if isexpr(e, :(=))
1331 lhs = e.args[1]
1332 if isa(lhs, SlotNumber)
1333 lhs === arg && return nothing
1334 rhs = e.args[2]
1335 if rhs === def
1336 arg = lhs
1337 end
1338 end
1339 end
1340 end
1341 end
1342 return arg
1343 end
